Task4:
One situation where digital communication led to a problem was when a student sent an email to a professor using casual language and without a proper subject line. The email was not clear, and the request was not properly explained.
This situation shows how poor digital communication may lead to problems, including misunderstanding and a lack of professionalism.
To avoid problems, it is important to use a proper subject line, proper language, and a proper message structure. Proper communication practices are important for effective communication and for building a professional image.
Through this task, I have learned the importance of respectful digital communication.

Task5:
During the course of my research on cybercrime, I was most surprised by the fact that people can easily fall victims to such crimes by divulging crucial information such as OTP or UPI PIN. This is possible by the fact that most scammers employ the simplest of tactics to lure people into divulging such information. This makes them highly effective in their operations.
I also came to the conclusion that minor slip-ups such as clicking on unknown links or responding to suspicious messages can lead to substantial financial losses. This also makes one more aware of the risks involved in the process.
So, one habit I am going to develop is to be more careful while using digital platforms. This is going to be helpful for me in the future to remain safe while using digital platforms.

